cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the construction of binary de Bruijn sequences, which are important in coding theory and information theory. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of cycles and trees in the adjacency graph of an LFSR, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a method for efficiently generating de Bruijn sequences, which involves identifying conjugate pairs and constructing trees, both of which are fundamental data structures in computer science. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves the use of Zech's logarithms, which are a tool in finite field arithmetic and numerical analysis. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of LFSRs, which are commonly used in control systems and digital signal processing.
